ZCZC GE65
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
TUESDAY TO FRIDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 132300 UTC
ON TUESDAY AN ANTICYCLONE CENTRED HUMBER 1030 WILL MOV
SLWY EWARDS TO NERN GERMANY WITH LITTLE CHANGE BY
WEDNESDAY AFTERNOON AND THEN DRIFT SLWY AWAY SEWARDS ON
THURSDAY. PRESSURE WILL CONTINUE TO BE RELATIVELY LOW
ACROSS THE NORWEGIAN SEA WITH A LOW EXP TO DEVELOP ACROSS
SERN NORWAY ON THURSDAY AFTERNOON. THIS LOW WILL THEN
TRANSFER TO THE BALTIC SEA 1005 BY FRIDAY AFTERNOON. AN
ANTICYCLONE WILL THEN BECOME CENTRED FASTNET 1022 BY THE
SAME TIME WITH A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE EXTENDING
NEWARDS ACROSS NORWAY. WINDS WILL GENERALLY BE LIGHT
ACROSS MOST AREAS BEFORE THEN INCR STRG S N OF 55 N
OVERNIGHT. WINDS MAY INCREASE FURTHER TO REACH NEAR GALE
FORCE ACROSS N VIKING AND N UTSIRE ON WEDNESDAY MORNING.
WINDS WILL THEN BECOME MORE W ACROSS ALL AREAS ON
THURSDAY AND CONTINUE STRG FOR A TIME IN NERN AREAS.
WINDS DECR OVERNIGHT WITH WINDS BECMG LIGHT DURING FRIDAY
NNNN